# AWS S3 Public Access Risk Analysis

## What I did:

- Tested public access using object URL
- Verified access from incognito mode
- Shared link to confirm unrestricted access

---

## Key Learnings:

- Public access requires no authentication
- Anyone with the link can access the data
- Data can be indexed or shared unintentionally

---

## Hands-on Summary:

- Opened object URL in browser
- Verified access without AWS login
- Confirmed vulnerability

---

## Mistakes to Avoid:

- Assuming only limited users can access public data
- Ignoring access testing after configuration changes

---

## Security Insight:

- Public exposure can lead to:
  - Data leaks
  - Compliance violations
  - Reputation damage

---

